d the nursing profession, one of the most challenging and underappreciated jobs in the world. Often, nursing demands technical expertise; sometimes, as these stories reveal, patients also need something more basic: a hand to hold, or someone to listen closely. Being on the front lines of medicine requires empathy, fortitude, knowledge, and grace. Nurses, now, more than ever, are the backbone of the healthcare system, the first line in providing the best possible care for all patients. 0aNursesvBiography. 0aNurses' writings. 0aNursing. 7aNurses.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01041618 7aNurses' writings.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01041725 7aNursing.2fast0(OCoLC)fst01041731 2aNursesvBiography. 2aNursing. 7aEssays.2lcgft 7aCreative nonfiction.2lcgft 7aBiography.2fast 7aNurses' writings.2lcsh1 aGutkind, Lee,eeditor.1 aFeinstein, Karen Wolk,eeditor.  aBaker and TaylorbBTCPnBK0011854898  aYBP Library ServicesbYANKn9456697  aC0bWAU